Jenkins:-- Jenkin is an open-source project written in JAVA by'Kohsuke Kawaguchi' it runs on the window,linux & Macos.
      It is community-supported,free to use and the first choice for continuous integration.
---> Consis of plugins
      [ Plugin: Plugin system that allows developers to write plugins affecting nearly every aspect of Jenkins behavior.
        Special add-ons that extend Jenkins capabilities with over (2000) plugins avilabel,tat make workflows more efficient & easier to manage.
---> Automates the entire s/w development life cycle.
---> It was originally developed by 'Sun Microsystem in 2004 as 'HUDSON'
    1. The project was renamed Jenkins when oracle brought the microsystem.
    2. It can run on any major platform without compatibility issues.
    3. Whenever developers write code, we integrate all the code of all developers at any point in time & we build,test,,deliver/deplay it to the 
        client,This is called CI/CD.

Continuous Integration(CI):----
      Whenever a developer commits the code using source code management like Git,then the CI pipline gets the changes of the code ru
automatically build and unit test.
---> Due to integrating the new code with old code, we can easily get to know the code is a success or failure.
---> It finds the errors more quickly.
---> Delivery the products to client more frequentlt.
---> Developers don't need to manual tasks.
---> Reduces the developers time 20% to 30%.

Continuous Delivery/Deployment(CD):----
      Continuous delivery is making it available deployment.Anytime a new build artifact is available,the artifact is automatically placed in 
the desired environment & deployed.
      Continuous Deployment is when you commit your code then it gets automatically tested, build & deploy on the production server.

Continuous intergration:--
                              *****Continous Delivery*****
Build->Test->Deplot to staging->Acceptance tests-> Deploy to production-> Smoke Test.
------------------------------------------------   --------------------    -----------
                        |                                  |                  |
                  Autimation                             manual            Automation
                               *****Continous Deployment***** 
Build->Test->Deplot to staging->Acceptance tests-> Deploy to production-> Smoke Test.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                          |
                                      Automation

1.Version Control:- Here developers need to write code for web applications. so it needs to be committed using version control system like Git or SVN.
                    Git is a distributed system  where every developer has a full opy of the repository,whilw SVN is a centralized system where a single server holds the master copy.
2.Build:- Lets consider your code is written in JAVA, it needs to be compiled before execution. In this build step code gets compiled.
3.Unit Test:- If the build step is completed,then move to testing phase in this step unit step will be done.
4.Deploy:- If the test step is completed, then move to deploy phase in this step you can deploy your code in dev,testing environment. Here you can see your application output.
5.Auto Test:- Once our code is working fine in testing servers,Then we need to do automation testing using selenium or Junit.
                [Selenium & Junit are not competing tools but rather complementory once used together in automated testing 
                 Selenium->Browser Automation Tool->Remote control webdrive Grid
                 Junit->Unit tesing Frame work.]
6.Deploy to production:-If everthing is fine then you can directly deploy your code in production server.

Note: If we have error in code then it will give feedback and it will be corrected, if we have error in build then it give feedback & it will be corrected,
      pipline will work like this unit it reaches deploy.Because of this pipline,bugs will be reported fast & get rectified so entire development in fast.
